{"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CGVector","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGVector","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"By default, the center point of an annotation view is placed at the geographic","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"coordinate point of the associated annotation. If you do not want the view to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"be centered, you can use this property to reposition the view. The offset’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"dx","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dy"},{"type":"text","text":" values are measured in points. Positive offset values move the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"annotation view down and to the right, while negative values move it up and to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the left."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Set the offset if the annotation view’s visual center point is somewhere other","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"than the logical center of the view. For example, the view may contain an image"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that depicts a downward-pointing pushpin or thumbtack, with the tip positioned","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at the center-bottom of the view. In that case, you would set the offset’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to zero and its ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dy"},{"type":"text","text":" to half the height of the view."}]}]}],"metadata":{"remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native\/blob\/main\/platform\/ios\/src\/MLNAnnotationView.h#L159","fileName":"MLNAnnotationView.h"},"symbolKind":"property","title":"centerOffset","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNAnnotationView(py)centerOffset","fragments":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}]},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}],"title":"MapLibre"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","title":"MLNAnnotationView","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"object that corresponds to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"text":" protocol. When an annotation’s","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"offscreen.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotationView","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"objects to handle the display.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","kind":"symbol","title":"MLNAnnotation"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/centerOffset":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","type":"topic","title":"centerOffset","abstract":[{"text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}]}}}